; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures USART as SPI and receives data.
;
; B. Preparation
;    Connecting ports with a suitable instrument should be correct
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. USART
;    2. PCU/GPIO
;
; D. Default Port
;    1. USART1  : PA11 (Slave Select)
;               : PA10 (Serial Clock)
;               : PA13 (Master Out Slave In)
;               : PA12 (Master In Slave Out)
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; USART1
; 1. Channel                   : 1 (USART1)
;
; 2. Config                    : [ 1 i s s m l e 5 ]
;    Operation                 : i (Interrupt)
;    USART Mode                : s (SPI)
;    SPI Mode                  : s (Slave)
;    Bit Order                 : m (MSB)
;    Polarity                  : l (Low)
;    Phase                     : e (Even Edge)
;    Baudrate                  : 5
;
; 3. Rx                        : [ 1 8 ]
;    Receive Data Length       : 8
;
; PCU (PAx)
; 1. Port Group                : 0 (PCU Port A)
;
; 2. Port                      : [ 0 10 a 3 ] [ 0 11 a 3 ] [ 0 12 a 3 ] [ 0 13 a 3 ]
;    Pin Number                : 10 / 11 / 12 / 13
;    Pin Mode                  : a (Alternative)
;    Alternative               : 3 (SCK11/SS11/MOSI11/MISO11)
;
; PCU (PAx)
sendln 'cm pcu'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 0 10 a 3 -pupd p'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 0 11 a 3 -pupd p'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 0 12 a 3 -pupd p'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 0 13 a 3 -pupd p'
mpause 30

; USART1
sendln 'cm usart'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 1'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 1'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 1 i s s m l e 5'
mpause 30
sendln 'rx 1 8'
